        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>As the eco­nomic and so­cial fall­out from the pan­demic con­tin­ues to bite, the 21 tem­po­rary shel­ters for the home­less in Sin­ga­pore are mostly full, with about 100 peo­ple on the wait list. There are two main rea­sons for the cur­rent short­age of shel­ter space: in­creased de­mand and re­duced num­ber of Safe Sound Sleep­ing Places.</p>

